\subsection{Posterior simulation and uncertainty estimation: \texttt{postsamples}}
In order to simulate observations from the posterior distribution of the regression coefficients, the function \texttt{postsamples} can be used. The type of analysis must be mentioned. The code below shows its use.

\footnotesize  
\begin{verbatim}
> Postsamples <- postsamples( nsample=50, n, grid, glmmap$GLMCoefStandardized[,,,k],
                 wavecoefglmmap$WaveletCoefficientMatrix,  hyperest$hyperparam, 
                 pkljbar$pkljbar, "multi", seed=123)
> names(Postsamples)
[1] "samples"       "postdiscovery"
> dim(Postsamples$samples)
[1]  3 32 32 50
> dim(Postsamples$postdiscovery)
[1]  3 32 32
\end{verbatim} 
\normalsize 

The argument \texttt{nsample} denotes the number of samples to be drawn. We can see \texttt{postsamples} returns the posterior samples and the probabilities of posterior discovery \citep{morris:et:al:2011} for all the subjects. Figure~\ref{fig:PostDiscovery}, obtained by the following code, shows the posterior discovery images based on the above 50 samples for the 3 subjects.

\footnotesize  
\begin{verbatim}
par(mfrow=c(1,n))
for(subject in 1:n)
  image(Postsamples$postdiscovery[subject,,], col=heat.colors(8),
   main=paste0("Subject ",subject))
\end{verbatim} 
\normalsize 

\begin{figure}[H]
	\centering
		\includegraphics[width=6in,height=2in]{PostDiscovery.pdf}
	\vspace{-1cm}
	\caption{Posterior discovery images for the 3 subjects.}
	\label{fig:PostDiscovery}
\end{figure}

From the posterior samples, the posterior standard deviations of the regression coefficients can be computed as follows.

\footnotesize  
\begin{verbatim}
> postsd <- array(dim=c(n,grid,grid))
> for(subject in 1:n)
   postsd[subject,,] <- apply(Postsamples$samples[subject,,,], 1:2, sd)
> round(postsd[1,1:5,1:5],3)
      [,1]  [,2]  [,3]  [,4]  [,5]
[1,] 0.466 0.496 0.471 0.677 0.677
[2,] 0.655 0.737 0.531 0.677 0.687
[3,] 0.657 0.465 0.472 0.435 0.656
[4,] 0.656 0.702 0.470 0.581 0.597
[5,] 0.571 0.468 0.417 0.532 0.508
\end{verbatim} 
\normalsize 

\subsection{Posterior group estimates: \texttt{postgroupglmcoef}}
Posterior group coefficients can be obtained by using the function \texttt{postgroupglmcoef} as follows. 

\footnotesize  
\begin{verbatim}
> postgroup <- postgroupglmcoef( n, grid, glmmap$GLMCoefStandardized[,,,k], 
               postwavecoefglmmap$PostMeanWaveletCoef)
> names(postgroup)
[1] "PostMeanReconsgroup"
> dim(postgroup$groupcoef)
[1] 32 32
\end{verbatim} 
\normalsize 

Figure \ref{fig:PostGroupCoef}, obtained by the following code, shows the posterior group coefficient image for the simulated dataset.

\footnotesize  
\begin{verbatim}
